A man died after he sustained a gunshot wound to the chest and was left in a field in Muvhango Extension 14 in Bophelong on Saturday.On arrival ER24 paramedics found the man delieved to be in his 20s lying in the field with SAPS members in attendance.Paramedics found that he had sustained several gunshot wounds to his chest and arms and was in a critical condition.Immediately Paramedics began treatment and provided the patient with several advanced life support interventions.The patient was transported to a nearby hospital. Sadly on route to hospital, the patients vital signs diminished and was declared dead.The exact cause of the incident are not yet known.-TNA Reporter 